{"title_page": "ADAM Architecture", "text_new": "[[File:Front_of_Millennium_Gate.jpg|thumb|[[Millennium Gate]] in [[Atlanta|Atlanta, Georgia, USA]] (2008)]]\n'''ADAM Architecture''' is an [[architecture]] and [[urban design]] practice in the UK with offices in [[Winchester]] and London.  The practice specialises in contemporary [[Traditional architecture|traditional]] and [[Classical architecture|classical]] design, commonly known as [[New Classical Architecture]].\n\nThe Practice was established in Winchester in 1955 as ''Evans, Roberts and Partners'', and Robert Adam joined the practice in 1977.<ref name=\"Search1\">John, Richard (2010). Robert Adam: The Search for a Modern Classicism. Mulgrave: The Images Publishing Group Pty Ltd, p.164</ref> The practice became incorporated in 1986 as ''Winchester Design'' and the name was changed to ''Robert Adam Architects'' in 2000.<ref name=\"AdamArchProfile\">Adam Architecture. \"Professor Robert Adam, Director\". Available online at [https://www.adamarchitecture.com]. Accessed 23 March 2018.</ref> The practice name changed to ''ADAM Architecture'' in March 2010. At the beginning of April 2020, Robert Adam stepped down as a Director of ADAM Architecture and will become an independent consultant. The practice remains equally owned by the shareholding directors: Nigel Anderson, Hugh Petter, George Saumarez Smith and Robbie Kerr. \n\nThe practice works on projects throughout Britain, the USA, continental Europe, the Middle East, India and Japan. The team of around 75 staff includes [[architect]]s, technologists, [[urban designer]]s, project managers, craftspeople, administrative support staff, and [[Dan Cruickshank]] as historic building consultant.\n\nRobert Adam was awarded the renowned [[Driehaus Architecture Prize]] in 2017.\n\n==Members of Traditional Architecture Group==\nMembers of Traditional Architecture Group (TAG) at ADAM Architecture include:<ref>{{cite web|title=Partners at ADAM Architecture|url=http://www.traditionalarchitecture.co.uk/memberslists.html|publisher=Traditional Architecture Group|accessdate=4 April 2014}}</ref>\n* Ian Aburrow \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Nigel Anderson \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Peter Cooke \u2013 London\n* Peter Critoph \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Akos Ginder \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Jasmin Harris \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Mark Himmens \u2013 London\n* Alex Montague-Smith \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Tom Orr \u2013 London\n* Hugh Petter \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Darren Price \u2013 London\n* Wayne Reakes \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* George Saumarez Smith \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Diana Yu \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n\n==Notable projects==\n\n*[[File:SacklerLibrary.jpg|thumb|[[Sackler Library]] for [[Oxford University]], Oxford, UK]]\n*[[Sackler Library]] for [[Oxford University]], Oxford, UK (2001) \u2013 designed by Robert Adam\n*[[Millennium Gate]] Atlanta, USA (2008) \u2013 designed by Hugh Petter\n*[[Stocks House]] renovation, Hertfordshire, UK (2008) \u2013 restoration by Hugh Petter\n*William Wake House, [[Northamptonshire]], UK (2010) \u2013 on completion, the largest new classical building in Britain for over 50 years.<ref>[http://www.traditionalarchitecture.co.uk/ Largest classical building in Britain for over 50 years now complete], Traditional Architecture Group, November 2011. Retrieved 2012-01-16.</ref><ref>Jonathan Reilly, [http://www.northampton-news-hp.co.uk/News/Northampton-News/Facility-to-provide-vital-care-services.htm ''Facility to provide vital care services''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407074842/http://www.northampton-news-hp.co.uk/News/Northampton-News/Facility-to-provide-vital-care-services.htm |date=2014-04-07 }}, Herald & Post (Northampton), 4 November 2010. Retrieved 2012-01-16.</ref>\n*[[RAF Bentley Priory#Redevelopment|RAF Bentley Priory]], Stanmore near London \u2013 restoration and new housing, designed by Nigel Anderson\n*[[Western Harbour, Edinburgh|Western Harbour]], Leith near Edinburgh \u2013 a new residential area, masterplanned by Robert Adam\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n* [http://www.adamarchitecture.com www.adamarchitecture.com]\n* https://www.trinity.ox.ac.uk/levinebuilding/ New  Levine Building at Trinity College, Oxford\n* [http://www.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/sackler/ Sackler Library, Oxford]\n* [http://www.adamarchitecture.com/images/PDFs/Times-Bond%20St_Nov-2011-01s.pdf New gallery restores the artistic heart to Bond Street], The Times, 19 November 2011\n* New name for traditionalist Robert Adam, [http://www.architectsjournal.co.uk/news/daily-news/new-name-for-traditionalist-robert-adam/5215956.article Architect's Journal], 30 March 2010\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120425152640/http://www.brick.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/BB-Autumn-2011.pdf ADAM Architecture profiled in the Brick Bulletin] Autumn 2011, produced by the Brick Development Association\n* [http://www.adamarchitecture.com/images/PDFs/Daily_Telegraph-Dec2008-01.pdf We must learn to build a better Britain], article by Clive Aslet, the Daily Telegraph, 4 December 2008\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|ADAM Architecture}}\n*[http://www.adamarchitecture.com ADAM Architecture] official website\n*[https://www.theguardian.com/money/2006/jul/24/careers.theguardian5 ''Hidden Passions''], The Guardian, 24 July 2006\n*The Country House Ideal \u2013 Recent Work by [https://www.gdcinteriors.com/adam-architecture/ ADAM Architecture]\n\n{{authority control}}\n{{Driehaus Prize laureates}}\n\n\n[[Category:Architecture firms of England]]\n[[Category:British neoclassical architects]]\n[[Category:New Classical architects]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Front_of_Millennium_Gate.jpg|thumb|[[Millennium Gate]] in [[Atlanta|Atlanta, Georgia, USA]] (2008)]]\n'''ADAM Architecture''' is an [[architecture]] and [[urban design]] practice in the UK with offices in [[Winchester]] and London.  The practice specialises in contemporary [[Traditional architecture|traditional]] and [[Classical architecture|classical]] design, commonly known as [[New Classical Architecture]].\n\nThe Practice was established in Winchester in 1955 as ''Evans, Roberts and Partners'', and Robert Adam joined the practice in 1977.<ref name=\"Search1\">John, Richard (2010). Robert Adam: The Search for a Modern Classicism. Mulgrave: The Images Publishing Group Pty Ltd, p.164</ref> The practice became incorporated in 1986 as ''Winchester Design'' and the name was changed to ''Robert Adam Architects'' in 2000.<ref name=\"AdamArchProfile\">Adam Architecture. \"Professor Robert Adam, Director\". Available online at [https://www.adamarchitecture.com/robert-adam,-director.htm]. Accessed 23 March 2018.</ref> The practice name most recently changed to ''ADAM Architecture'' in March 2010. The practice works on projects throughout Britain, the USA, continental Europe, the Middle East, India and Japan. The team of around 75 staff includes [[architect]]s, technologists, [[urban designer]]s, project managers, craftspeople, administrative support staff, and [[Dan Cruickshank]] as historic building consultant.\n\nThere are six directors: Robert Adam, Nigel Anderson, Paul Hanvey, Robbie Kerr, Hugh Petter and George Saumarez Smith. Robert Adam was awarded the renowned [[Driehaus Architecture Prize]] in 2017.\n\n==Members of Traditional Architecture Group==\nMembers of Traditional Architecture Group (TAG) at ADAM Architecture include:<ref>{{cite web|title=Partners at ADAM Architecture|url=http://www.traditionalarchitecture.co.uk/memberslists.html|publisher=Traditional Architecture Group|accessdate=4 April 2014}}</ref>\n* Ian Aburrow \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Robert Adam \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Nigel Anderson \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* John Bulford \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Peter Cooke \u2013 London\n* Peter Critoph \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Akos Ginder \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Jasmin Harris \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Mark Himmens \u2013 London\n* Alex Montague-Smith \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* David Myres \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Tom Orr \u2013 London\n* Hugh Petter \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Darren Price \u2013 London\n* Wayne Reakes \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* George Saumarez Smith \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n* Diana Yu \u2013 Hampshire, Winchester\n\n==Notable projects==\n[[File:SacklerLibrary.jpg|thumb|[[Sackler Library]] for [[Oxford University]], Oxford, UK]]\n*[[Sackler Library]] for [[Oxford University]], Oxford, UK (2001) \u2013 designed by Robert Adam\n*[[Millennium Gate]] Atlanta, USA (2008) \u2013 designed by Hugh Petter\n*[[Stocks House]] renovation, Hertfordshire, UK (2008) \u2013 restoration by Hugh Petter\n*William Wake House, [[Northamptonshire]], UK (2010) \u2013 on completion, the largest new classical building in Britain for over 50 years.<ref>[http://www.traditionalarchitecture.co.uk/ Largest classical building in Britain for over 50 years now complete], Traditional Architecture Group, November 2011. Retrieved 2012-01-16.</ref><ref>Jonathan Reilly, [http://www.northampton-news-hp.co.uk/News/Northampton-News/Facility-to-provide-vital-care-services.htm ''Facility to provide vital care services''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407074842/http://www.northampton-news-hp.co.uk/News/Northampton-News/Facility-to-provide-vital-care-services.htm |date=2014-04-07 }}, Herald & Post (Northampton), 4 November 2010. Retrieved 2012-01-16.</ref>\n*[[RAF Bentley Priory#Redevelopment|RAF Bentley Priory]], Stanmore near London \u2013 restoration and new housing, designed by Nigel Anderson\n*[[Western Harbour, Edinburgh|Western Harbour]], Leith near Edinburgh \u2013 a new residential area, masterplanned by Robert Adam\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n* [http://www.adamarchitecture.com www.adamarchitecture.com]\n* [http://www.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/sackler/ Sackler Library, Oxford]\n* [http://www.adamarchitecture.com/images/PDFs/Times-Bond%20S